        <section class="workout">
          <div id="ce_b-p">
            <div class="main-wt">
              <h4 class="main-wt-title">
                <span class="cursor" data-modal-target2="#modal72-11.">Bench Press</span>
                <div class="modal2" id="modal72-11.">
                  <div class="modal-header">
                    <button data-close-button class="close-button">&times;</button>
                  </div>
                  <div class="modal-body">
                    <div class="modal-p">
                      <img src="" alt="">
                    </div>
                  </div>
                </div>
                <div id="overlay"></div>
              </h4>
              <ul>
                <li class="basic-form" onclick="myFunction(event)">Standard Posture</li>
                <li>Shoulder packing - bringing the back together with chest extension</li>
                <li>Arch - Create an arch by pushing your back</li>
                <li>Eye - align with barbell</li>
                <li>Shoulder x 1.5 - grip slightly wider than shoulder width</li>
                <li>Grip Vertical - the bar in the hand is perpendicular to the forearm bones</li>
                <li>Leg Drive - Pushing the ribcage while pushing the feet in the direction of the upper body</li>
                <li>Barbell Position - Position the bar around the nipple</li>
                <li>Hand and arm vertical - When the arm is lowered, the hand and elbow are perpendicular to the ground
                </li>
                <li>Diagonal - slightly diagonal lift</li>
                <li>Abdominal Compression - Giving constant tension to the core</li>
              </ul>
              <div class="benefit">
                Effective for entire Chest
              </div>
              <div class="methods">
                <h4>Varioud Actions</h4>
                <div class="more-method">
                  <h4>Incline Bench Press</h4>
                  <p>Effective on the upper chest. shoulder packing. Shoulders should always be as low as possible.
                    Elbows slightly forward. Concentrate on lowering the barbell toward the collarbone (vertical). A
                    bench angle of 30 degrees is effective</p>
                </div>
                <div class="more-method">
                  <h4>Decline Bench Press</h4>
                  <p>Effective on the lower chest. However, even if you do a flat bench well, the lower chest is filled,
                    so it is not recommended</p>
                </div>
                <div class="more-method">
                  <h4>Dumbbell Bench Press</h4>
                  <p>Increased range of motion. Keep the shoulder girdle fixed at all times(so that the shoulder is not
                    lifted). Raise the dumbbells while bringing your chest together(keep your biceps as close to your
                    chest as possible and straighten your elbows)</p>
                </div>
                <div class="more-method">
                  <h4>Smith Machine Bench Press</h4>
                  <p>Because the trajectory is fixed, it hinders the development of stabilizer muscles. So, I do not
                    recommend this exercise except for intermediate and advanced users for isolating specific parts</p>
                </div>
                <div class="more-method">
                  <h4>Leg Lift Bench Press</h4>
                  <p>Core(stabilizing muscle) involvement is high and muscle activity is also high. However, the output
                    value drops due to high instability. Not recommended unless you are advanced</p>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>


